{"TopicId":170838,"ForumId":15,"TopicTitle":"jagged texture edges?","CreatedByName":"/not/pol/","CreatedById":172548,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-12T17:24:31Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"/not/pol/","CreatedById":172548,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-12T17:24:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTextures always seem super sharp and jagged, even for a 1024x1024 file.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022aUOI3Vg.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/aUOI3Vg.png\u0022 width=\u0022934\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CobaltWolf","CreatedById":105588,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-12T17:29:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you checked them in Unity? Textures will filter differently in engine, I notice that they tend to be less apparent in Unity than in my modeling program (Maya)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"/not/pol/","CreatedById":172548,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-12T17:38:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223293243\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170838\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221518456554\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105588\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CobaltWolf\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, CobaltWolf said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you checked them in Unity? Textures will filter differently in engine, I notice that they tend to be less apparent in Unity than in my modeling program (Maya)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHm, i\u0027ll try that, i still need to add a noise map anyways.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}